# Swish — Cursor rules
# These are example project rules. Edit or remove sections as your workflow evolves.

## Project overview

Swish is a C++17 Vulkan renderer with deferred lighting, bloom, and a modular scene system.
Key areas: `src/renderer/` (Vulkan pipeline), `src/scene/` (camera, scenes, models), `src/core/` (app/window), `shaders/` (GLSL), `config/` (TOML baked to binary).

## Code style

- Follow Google C++ style as configured in `.clang-format` (4-space indent, 120 col limit, left pointer alignment).
- Run `./scripts/format.sh` after editing C++ headers or sources.
- All code lives in `namespace swish`.
- Use type aliases from `src/utils/Types.h` (`Vec3`, `Mat4`, etc.) instead of raw `glm::` types in application code.
- Prefer `#pragma once` guards; one class per header/source pair.

## File and module layout

- Place each component in its own folder: `ComponentName/ComponentName.h` and `ComponentName/ComponentName.cpp`.
- Keep renderer managers registered through `Renderer` / `RendererServices` — do not create parallel global singletons.
- Add new `.cpp` files to `CMakeLists.txt` under the `swish` executable target.
- Use relative includes within a module (e.g. `../SceneGeometry/SceneGeometry.h`), not absolute paths.

## Vulkan and rendering

- Do not call Vulkan APIs directly from scene code; route through renderer managers (`TextureManager`, `ScenePipeline`, `PostProcessManager`, etc.).
- When adding shaders: add the `.vert`/`.frag` under `shaders/`, register it in `SHADER_SOURCES` in `CMakeLists.txt`, and load the compiled `.spv` via `SHADER_DIR`.
- Respect existing descriptor set layout: set 0 = camera/lights, set 1 = PBR material textures.
- Check `VkResult` return values; use existing error-handling patterns in `VulkanContext` and `Device`.

## Scenes and assets

- Scene configuration goes in TOML under `config/` and is baked to binary at build time — do not hardcode scene parameters in C++ when a TOML field exists.
- Textures live in `textures/` or `assets/`; reference them via `TEXTURE_DIR` or existing loader utilities (`StbImage`, `TextureManager`).
- Preserve `WORLD_SCALE` (1000.0f) conventions when converting between scene units and world space.

## Build and test

- Build with CMake; macOS uses `build-xcode/` or an out-of-source build directory — never commit build artifacts.
- Requires Vulkan SDK (`glslc` on PATH). Shaders compile automatically via the `shaders` custom target.
- Run tests with `ctest` from the build directory after meaningful changes to `src/utils/` or shared logic.
- Do not modify files under `build-xcode/`, `include/glad.c`, or vendored headers unless explicitly asked.

## Change discipline

- Keep diffs focused — match the scope of the request; avoid drive-by refactors.
- Do not add comments that restate what the code already says; comment only non-obvious Vulkan lifetime, synchronization, or pipeline ordering details.
- Do not create git commits or push unless explicitly requested.
